categories.name: Artistique
categories.description: Client: Riding Cities, skateboard association; Mission: Update the Riding Cities website as follows:1. Create a new section, The Founding Members, with the names and photos of the association's creators.2. Modify the section containing the Download Class Schedule button to add a title and two buttons for downloading two different class schedules (one for children and one for adults). Information about the code: Only HTML code needs to be developed. The existing code contains lines that can be reused and adapted to achieve the layout shown in the mockup. The CSS code is already in place, and you should copy and paste the existing CSS classes to style and format the elements as shown in the mockup.

categories.description: Spécialisée dans la photo intimiste, je vous invite dans mon univers sensuel et émotionnel. Je réalise aussi pour vous des portraits plus classiques doux et expressif.

categories.name: Boudoir
categories.description: My mission is to develop a mobile-first website that catalogs the menus of gourmet restaurants. In addition to the traditional reservation systems, customers will be able to customize their meal menu so that the dishes are ready upon their arrival. Say goodbye to waiting times at the restaurant!

categories.name: Extérieur
categories.description: The purpose of this project is to introduce you to the JavaScript programming language, which is highly popular among web developers. It is very structured and will guide you step by step in acquiring the fundamentals of the language. You will soon use it to develop more ambitious websites, but initially, take your first steps with JavaScript... Ideally, completing this project will take you 1 to 2 weeks at most (if you are dedicating full-time to your training). You will be exclusively supported by your mentor, both for the deliverables' completion and for the presentation, which will take the form of a discussion.

categories.name: Grossesse
categories.description: I must develop: 1. The presentation page of the architect's work (using the provided HTML as a starting point). 2. The site administrator's (the client's) login page (code to be created from scratch). 3. The modal for uploading new media (code to be created from scratch).
